            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A planetary surface is a surface layer where the solid or liquid material of a planet comes into contact with an atmosphere or outer space.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:comment>a useful class: this can be used to define sub-terrestrial and sub-marine entities</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>planetary surface</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


