            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A boundary layer is a layer of fluid in the immediate vicinity of a bounding surface where the effects of viscosity are significant enough to distort the surrounding non-viscous flow.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:created_by>ORCID:0000-0002-4366-3088</oboInOwl:created_by>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>boundary layer</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
