        <oboInOwl:inSubset>envoMarine</oboInOwl:inSubset>
        <oboInOwl:inSubset xml:lang="en">envoPlastics</oboInOwl:inSubset>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">At this level, the depth of this layer is ambiguous. Some methods (telemetry) measure only the first few centimeters of the sea or ocean surface. In situ methods often sample the first few meters. Subclasses can be created for such cases.
Sea surface layer is also used to refer to the surfaces of oceans.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">sea surface layer</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


